      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "As a former federal law enforcement officer, I share Virginians' concerns about federal immigration enforcement officers wearing masks on American streets — undercutting basic expectations of accountability, sowing fear and confusion, and eroding public trust.\n\nKids afraid to get on the school bus. Workers not showing up to their jobs. Neighbors scared to go to the grocery store.\n\nThat's what aggressive federal immigration enforcement is doing to Virginia communities.\n\nToday, I signed Executive Order 16 to:\n🔹 Ban ICE from using state property as an operations base\n🔹 Require federal immigration officers to show warrants before accessing state property\n🔹 Launch a Know Your Rights website for Virginians affected by federal immigration enforcement to access resources and guidance\n🔹 Provide guidance for employees at courthouses, schools, polling locations, and healthcare facilities when federal officers attempt to conduct immigration enforcement",
      "text_resolved": "As a former federal law enforcement officer, I share Virginians' concerns about federal immigration enforcement officers wearing masks on American streets — undercutting basic expectations of accountability, sowing fear and confusion, and eroding public trust.\n\nKids afraid to get on the school bus. Workers not showing up to their jobs. Neighbors scared to go to the grocery store.\n\nThat's what aggressive federal immigration enforcement is doing to Virginia communities.\n\nToday, I signed Executive Order 16 to:\n🔹 Ban ICE from using state property as an operations base\n🔹 Require federal immigration officers to show warrants before accessing state property\n🔹 Launch a Know Your Rights website for Virginians affected by federal immigration enforcement to access resources and guidance\n🔹 Provide guidance for employees at courthouses, schools, polling locations, and healthcare facilities when federal officers attempt to conduct immigration enforcement",
